Citation.sAbstract: In the present work, temperature dependence of heat capacity of methylprednisolone aceponate has been measured for the first time over the range from 7 K to 346 K by precision adiabatic vacuum calorimetry. Based on the experimental results, the thermodynamic functions of the methylprednisolone aceponate, namely, the heat capacity, enthalpy H (T) H (0), entropy S (T) S (0) and Gibbs function G (T) H (0) have been determined for the range from T/K0 333. The enthalpy of combustion ( 14304.4 +- 9.1) kJ mol 1 of the methylprednisolone aceponate was determined for the first time using high-precision combustion calorimeter. The standard molar enthalpy of formation in the crystalline state ( 1465.3 +- 9.8) kJ mol 1 of compound at 298.15 K was derived from the combustion experiments. Using a combination of the adiabatic and combustion calorimetry results the thermodynamic functions of formation of the folic acid dihydrate at T = 298.15 K and p = 0.1 MPa have been calculated.
